caption: The sound of water, the carvings on the wall, the mother and child statue, it was 1 a.m., but time was passing very slowly. It might be a good place to think.
One of the rare vestiges of a vanished Paris....Always a great discovery for tourists who wander through the neighborhood
Rue de Jarente is magnificent, and this fountain still adds charm!
Vestige of a vanished era in an alley which has preserved its cobblestones of yesteryear.
It almost goes unnoticed in the alley where it is located.
